The paper discusses the construction of efficient internal sorting algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL). The use of external sorting algorithms also suggests a connection to database management (cs.DM). The analysis of the number of comparisons made during sorting relates to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT).
